    "headline": "Of All The Trees, In All The Schools, In All The Districts, She Nests Right Here",
    "body": "Every year The Guthrie Center trees are home to a variety of nesting birds - mostly grackles and doves . While the former tends to build their nests in our tall trees (and are very protective of their territory), the doves seem to find areas closer to the ground. A few years ago a pair tried to build their nest in one of our water fountains; this year they are in the potted palm on our deck.",
