    "year": 2011,
    "headline": "Guthrie Teacher Of The Year",
    "body": "Congratulations to Christy Capps who has been chosen by her peers as our Teacher of the Year. Christy teaches Agricultural Science and in addition to her teaching assignment, also manages the FFA program along with fellow teacher Vanessa Collier. Christy came to Spring Branch in the summer of 2009 after teaching in Normangee. She grew up in the Cy-Fair school district, in the Cypress Creek Agriculture department. Christy is a Sam Houston State University Agriculture graduate who student taught at Waller High School and was later hired to run the Waller Junior High agriculture department.",
