    "date": "2011-02-07",
    "year": 2011,
    "headline": "Her Character Is Without Question",
    "body": "Congratulations to Ambar Balderas , recipient of this year’s Character Without Question Award for The Guthrie Center. Recently, outstanding students were nominated by their instructors for this prestigious honor, based on characteristics such as honest and integrity, responsibility, dependability, respect, perseverance, courage, caring and kindness, citizenship and civic virtue. Nominees for the award included Ambar Balderas, Justin Tung, Mariana Rivero-Loyola, Walter Mata, Christine Nguyen, David Unrath, Kate Denninger and Moriah Elizando . The students, all deserving of their nomination, were interviewed by a committee last week. Ambar will be recognized at the Spring Branch Board of Trustees Meeting on March 28 th along with the other awardees from schools throughout the district. Ambar had another great piece of news arrive last week in the mail - her official letter of Appointment to The United States Naval Academy , where she will attend following her graduation from Northbrook High School in May.",
