    "year": 2011,
    "headline": "Guthrie Staff Recognized For Service",
    "body": "Last night many of our Guthrie teachers and staff were recognized for their service and retirement at the 2011 SBISD Awards Banquet at the Omni Hotel Westide , hosted by the SBISD Community Relations and Communications department. Congratulations to all of our milestone makers: Robotics instructor Joe Lynch who was honored as he retires after 20 years Counselor Beverly Litton for her 40 years of service Administrative assistant Elva Saldivar , NJROTC instructor Col. Ken Sluis and Computer Tech instructor Steve Whitt for 15 years Architectural Design instructor Sonia Greiner , attendance specialist Donna Benavidez and CTE instructional support Melissa Sanders for 10 years Library support Carla Stevens for completing five years Board member Wayne Schaper was honored for his 50 years in the district, In addition to being celebrated by many people, the highlight was a video filmed and produced by our Advanced Film students and teachers Mike Radler, Patty Nilsson and Michael Ortiz. (You can view the video here) We appreciate our staff and sincerely thank them for their sacrifices to help our students find themselves and become successful, and are grateful to our district leaders and board for recognizing all those honored at the event.",
