    "id": "2013-05-09-7136",
    "date": "2013-05-09",
    "year": 2013,
    "headline": "Eight In A Row",
    "body": "For the eighth consecutive year, the Spring Branch Navy Junior ROTC program has earned the Distinguished with Academic Honors designation. This stems from excelling in their AMI, drill meets, air rifle meets, orienteering meets, leadership training, community service and more. Achieving it takes careful planning, preparation, execution and assessment of results. This honor allows the principal to nominate three eligible NJROTC cadets as candidates for appointment to the Naval Academy, Military Academy and Air Force Academy. Congratulations to our unit cadets and cadet leadership, outgoing Senior Naval Science Instructor Col. Ken Sluis and Master Chief Mark Heuser for creating and maintaining a strong, effective, well-run program.",
    "programs": [
      "NJROTC"
    ],
